<item>
            <title>[JXPATH-20] [jxpath] JXPathContext.removeAll() doesn&apos;t remove all (just one)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXPATH-20</link>
                <project id="12310480" key="JXPATH">Commons JXPath</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JXPathContext.removeAll() doesn&apos;t remove all items for a Collection path supplied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TestCase to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    public void testRemoveAllFromCollection() {&lt;br/&gt;
        final Map map = new HashMap();&lt;br/&gt;
        final Collection list = new ArrayList();&lt;br/&gt;
        for(int i = 0; i &amp;lt; 20; i++) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            list.add(&quot;&quot; + i);
        }
&lt;p&gt;        map.put( &quot;list&quot;, list);&lt;br/&gt;
        JXPathContext context = JXPathContext.newContext(null, map);&lt;br/&gt;
        context.removeAll( &quot;list&quot; );&lt;br/&gt;
        assertEquals(&quot;not all items removed&quot;, 0, list.size() );&lt;br/&gt;
    }&lt;/p&gt;</description>
